settings.title: Join 10,000+ Happy Australian Travellers!
settings.home_page_richtext: We have over 10,000+ happy Australian customers who have used our travel adapter to travel to all corners of the globe.

settings.title: 1 Adapter, 200+ Countries
settings.richtext:
Don't buy and carry around a pile of different adapters for every country you visit.

This compact travel adapter converts plugs to, and from, over 200+ different countries. 

Our adapter will work in every single country in Europe.

It will also work in every single country in Asia.

It will even work on your layover at the airport in Dubai or Singapore, so you can charge your devices between flights.

Since it works in over 200 of the 220 countries in the world, the chances are it will work wherever you go!

We have a full list of countries our adapter will work in further down this page.
settings.richtext_2:
Don't buy a seperate adapter for every device you and your family use overseas.

This adapter has 3 USB Port, 1 USB-C Port and a regular plug.

This means you can use it to charge up to 4 USB devices at the same time, and still use the power plug.

You could use the USB ports to charge 2 phones, a powerbank and a go-pro, while also using the plug to charge a laptop.

The plug outlet accepts Australian plugs, as well as plugs from over 200+ other countries.

settings.title: What countries will it work in?
settings.content_1:
Despite European countries using different plugs, our adapter will work in every country in Europe.

Australia and Europe also use the same voltage so you do not need to worry about a voltage converter.

Here's the list of countries in Europe our adapter will work in:

Albania, Andorra, Austria, Belarus, Belgium, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Bulgaria, Channel Islands, Croatia, Czechia, Denmark, Estonia, Faeroe Islands, Finland, France, Germany, Gibraltar, Greece, Hungary, Iceland, Ireland, Isle of Man, Italy, Latvia, Liechtenstein, Lithuania, Luxembourg, Malta, Moldova, Monaco, Montenegro, Netherlands, North Macedonia, Norway, Poland, Portugal, Romania, Russia, San Marino, Serbia, Slovakia, Slovenia, Spain, Sweden, Switzerland, Ukraine, United Kingdom
settings.content_2:
Despite Asian countries using different plugs, and some Asian countries even using multiple different plugs, our adapter will work in every country in Asia.

Aside from Japan, Australia and Asia also use the same voltage so you do not need to worry about a voltage converter.

If you travel to Japan, please check your devices are compatable with 110v before plugging them in as our adapter does not convert voltage.

Most appliances now are compatable with both 110v and 240v, but just make sure, the label should say 110-240v if it is.

You can use the USB ports on our adapter in Japan with no issue.

Here's the list of countries in Asia our adapter will work in:

(Countries that use 110v are marked with a *)

Afghanistan, Armenia, Azerbaijan, Bahrain, Bangladesh, Bhutan, Brunei Darussalam, Cambodia, China, Cyprus, Georgia, Hong Kong, India, Indonesia, Iran, Iraq, Israel, Japan*, Jordan, Kazakhstan, Kuwait, Kyrgyzstan, Laos, Lebanon, Macao, Malaysia, Maldives, Mongolia, Myanmar, Nepal, North Korea, Oman, Pakistan, Philippines, Qatar, Saudi Arabia, Singapore, South Korea, Sri Lanka, State of Palestine, Syria, Taiwan, Tajikistan, Thailand, Timor-Leste, Turkey, Turkmenistan, United Arab Emirates, Uzbekistan, Vietnam, Yemen
settings.content_3:
Despite North American countries using different plugs our adapter will work in every country in North America.

However, most countries in North America are a different voltage to Australia.

If you travel to North America, please check your devices are compatable with 110v before plugging them in as our adapter does not convert voltage.

Most appliances now are compatable with both 110v and 240v, but just make sure, the label should say 110-240v if it is.

You can use the USB ports on our adapter in these countries with no issue.

Here's the list of countries in North America our adapter will work in:

(Countries that use 110v are marked with a *)

Anguilla*, Antigua and Barbuda, Aruba*, Bahamas*, Barbados*, Belize*, Bermuda*, British Virgin Islands*, Canada*, Caribbean Netherlands*, Cayman Islands*, Costa Rica*, Cuba*, Curaçao*, Dominica, Dominican Republic*, El Salvador*, Greenland, Grenada, Guadeloupe, Guatemala*, Haiti*, Honduras*, Jamaica*, Martinique, Mexico*, Montserrat, Nicaragua*, Panama*, Puerto Rico*, Saint Barthélemy, Saint Kitts and Nevis, Saint Lucia, Saint Martin, Saint Pierre and Miquelon, Saint Vincent and the Grenadines*, Sint Maarten*, Trinidad and Tobago*, Turks and Caicos Islands*, U.S.A.*, United States Virgin Islands*
settings.content_4:
Despite South American countries using different plugs our adapter will work in every country in South America.

However, some countries in South America are a different voltage to Australia.

If you travel to South America, please check your devices are compatable with 110v before plugging them in as our adapter does not convert voltage.

Most appliances now are compatable with both 110v and 240v, but just make sure, the label should say 110-240v if it is.

You can use the USB ports on our adapter in these countries with no issue.

Here's the list of countries in South America our adapter will work in:

(Countries that use 110v are marked with a *)

Argentina, Bolivia, Brazil*, Chile, Colombia*, Ecuador*, Falkland Islands, French Guiana, Guyana*, Paraguay, Peru, Suriname*, Uruguay, Venezuela*
settings.content_5:
Despite Africain countries using different plugs, and some African countries even using multiple different plugs, our adapter will work in every country in Africa except Eswatini, Lesotho and Nambibia.

Aside from Liberia, Australia and Africa also use the same voltage so you do not need to worry about a voltage converter.

If you travel to Liberia, please check your devices are compatable with 110v before plugging them in as our adapter does not convert voltage.

Most appliances now are compatable with both 110v and 240v, but just make sure, the label should say 110-240v if it is.

You can use the USB ports on our adapter in Liberia with no issue.

Here is a list of countries in Africa our adapter will work in:

(Countries that use 110v are marked with a *)

Algeria, Angola, Benin, Botswana, Burkina Faso, Burundi, Cabo Verde, Cameroon, Central African Republic, Chad, Comoros, Congo, Côte d'Ivoire, Democratic Republic of the, Congo, Djibouti, Egypt, Equatorial Guinea, Eritrea, Ethiopia, Gabon, Gambia, Ghana, Guinea, Guinea-Bissau, Kenya, Liberia*, Libya, Madagascar, Malawi, Mali, Mauritania, Mauritius, Mayotte, Morocco, Mozambique, Niger, Nigeria, Réunion, Rwanda, Saint Helena, Sao Tome and Principe, Senegal, Seychelles, Sierra Leone, Somalia, South Africa, South Sudan, Sudan, Tanzania, Togo, Tunisia, Uganda, Western Sahara, Zambia, Zimbabwe
settings.content_6:
Our adapter will work in every country in Australasia.

Most countries in Australasia do not require adapters as they use the Australian plug. We have marked these on the list with **.

Countries marked with * use 110v power.

If you travel to one of the countries marked with an *, please check your devices are compatable with 110v before plugging them in as our adapter does not convert voltage.

Most appliances now are compatable with both 110v and 240v, but just make sure, the label should say 110-240v if it is.

You can use the USB ports on our adapter in these countries with no issue.

Here's the list of countries in Australasia our adapter will work in:

(Countries that use 110v are marked with a *)

(Countries that use the same plug type as Australia are marked with **)

American Samoa*, Australia**, Cook Islands**, Fiji**, French Polynesia**, Guam*, Kiribati**, Marshall Islands*, Micronesia*, Nauru**, New Caledonia, New Zealand**, Niue**, Northern Mariana Islands*, Palau*, Papua New Guinea**, Samoa**, Solomon Islands, Tokelau**, Tonga**, Tuvalu**, Vanuatu*, Wallis and Futuna Islands

settings.title: High Quality and Safe
settings.richtext:
This travel adapter is FCC, CE and RoHS certified.

It has a 6.3 Amp fuse, ensuring complete protection for you and your devices.

The fuse is also auto-resetting so you never need to replace it.
settings.richtext_2: The built-in safety shutters protect users and children from touching the live parts of the socket outlet. They also prevent dust from getting inside, and from accidentally only plugging in 1 side of an EU plug.

settings.title: Frequently Asked Questions
settings.content_1:
- Max Power: 630W at 100V, 1575W at 250V

- Input Voltage: 100-250V AC 50/60HZ

- Output: 5V 5.4A(Total), 3400mA shared, up to 2.4A/slot when used alone

- This plug adapter does not convert voltage(AC-AC)

- Every country has it's own voltage standard, please check the voltage of the country you are visiting. (Voltage converters are expensive, any similar travel adapter, even the ones which only convert one countries plug to another will not convert voltage either).

- No grounding, this travel adapter is for use with unearthed or double insulate appliances onlyIt does not convert voltage, but you can use the USB ports in countries with different voltage to Australia. Most countries have the same voltage as Australia. USA and Canada are the main ones who don't. (Voltage converters are expensive, any similar travel adapter, even the ones which only convert one countries plug to another will not convert voltage either).
settings.content_2:
No, it does not convert voltage, but you can use the USB ports in countries with different voltage to Australia.

Most countries have the same voltage as Australia.

USA and Canada are the main ones who don't. 

Voltage converters are expensive, any similar travel adapter, even the ones which only convert one countries plug to another will not convert voltage either.
settings.title_3: Will it work in this country?
settings.content_3:
Probably. The adaptor will work in over 150 countries so we arent going to list them all here.

You can check what the plug looks like in the country you are going to and compare it with the image above, but honestly chances are it will work.

It will cover you for Europe, Japan and Bali.

USA and Canada as well, however it won't convert voltage so do not use the power plug adaptor there, only the USB ports.
settings.title_4: Does it have a fuse to protect my devices?
settings.content_4:
Yes. It has a 6.3 amp fuse to protect your devices. It's also an auto-resetting fuse so you don't need to replace the fuse.

This is a great feature for countries that have less reliable and robust power networks.

All orders are shipped the same or next business day depending what time you place your order.

Domestic (Australia):

Australian orders are shipped from Melbourne, Victoria.

Standard Australian shipping is FREE for all orders, however you can choose to upgrade to express when you checkout.

International:

International orders are shipped from Melbourne, Victoria. International shipping prices are calculated when you checkout. International shipping prices are cheap, however we do not offer tracking on international orders to save costs, and while Australia post quotes delivery times to be around 12 days, they are known to be a lot longer sometimes depending on your location.
